name: Waxing Cream-Natural Color
description:
Instructions For Use: Work in a small area and apply waxing cream using a wax brush or lint-free cloth. Saturate the paint with waxing cream until it is a consistent color. Remove any excess wax. For a high shine, buff your piece while the wax is still wet using a lint-free cloth. Additional buffing 2-4 hours later will create an even harder surface.

Helpful Information:
-Freshly painted and finished surfaces should be kept free of moisture and extreme use for one week.
-Painted and finished surfaces take approximately one month to fully cure and harden.

Ingredients: Beeswax, clarified linseed oil, d-limonene, carnuba wax, essential oils, and lead-free dryers.

name: CeCe Caldwell "Bring a Piece" Workshop
description:
Bring a Piece $125.00
Saturday June 1st 10am-3pm
                     

You will learn the following advanced applications on your very own piece. 1) Painting/Layering 2) Crackling (2-3 applications) 3) Waxing and Finishing 

Light Lunch provided. 

Prerequisite: Intro Class

Wear clothing suitable to paint in. The piece should be capable of being carried in under your own power under your arm. Think smaller than a bread box. Example: Small accent table=ok, Cocktail table=not ok

name: CeCe Caldwell "Paint Made Easy" Introduction Workshop
description:
Get started painting with CeCe Caldwell’s Chalk & Clay Paints in this fun and technique-packed workshop! Virtually no prep is needed to paint over either new or existing furniture finishes. In this 2-1/2 hour workshop, students will paint multi-layered finishes on pieces of molding creating beautiful color combinations that are trending now for Vintage, French and Contemporary Décor. In addition to distressing the paint finish using a water resist technique that reveal bits of the previous layers, students will also be introduced to a distressed, not “contrived” finish. Finish with CeCe’s wonderful clear or dark waxes….and voila! Gorgeous molding pieces to take home and sample finishes to re-create on your furniture and decorative pieces at home! 
Workshop Fee $55 (includes all supplies) Prerequisite: None

name: Graphics Transfer Class
description:
Learn to create fun and current furniture looks using two different graphics transfer techniques. This workshop will teach you to transfer images to painted wood finishes and also on fabric. Using a blender pen and graphite transfer techniques you will learn applications that you can use to transform everyday items into extraordinary. Every wonder how to get those gorgeous looks you see all over Pinterest and in shelter magazines but for a fraction of the cost? Here is your chance! Judy Ainger of Vintage Street Designs specializes in repurposing items using chalk & clay paint and French transfers. This class provides everything you need. Come as you are and plan to leave inspired with the skill transform your own treasures!

Instructor: Judy Ainger of Vintage Street Designs
Workshop Fee $95 Prerequisite: None

name: Clear Glaze
description:
Instructions for use: CeCe Caldwell's Glaze is a versatile Glaze to be used straight from the can or tinted with pigments. To tint, mix with dry pigments to produce a colored glaze that works as a wash over your painted piece. CeCe Caldwell's clear glaze can be diluted up to a 1:4 ratio of glaze to water for a thinner glaze. For best results, tinted glaze should be applied over a satin finish or waxed surface. Finish with a light application of clear wax.

Helpful Information: 
-A glaze is not a durable finish by itself for most furniture items. Please use with CeCe Caldwell's clear wax or satin finish when a hard finish is needed
-Use at 55 degrees F or higher
-Do not allow to freeze
-CeCe Caldwells glaze is best applied with a brush, sponge or cloth
-This product requires 30 days to fully cure. Freshly glazed surfaces should be kept free from moisture and heavy use during that time. 

Ingredients: Cellulose, Alcohol Ester, Silica, Carnuba Wax, Clay, Water and Preservative

Approximate Coverage 290-590 sq ft

name: Satin Finish Pint, CeCe Caldwell’s
description: Satin Finish is CeCe's most durable topcoat option.  Made in the U.S.A.

name: Endurance Finish, CeCe Caldwells
description: Use 4-6 layers on surfaces such as a the tops of a family dining table, coffee table or end table. Endurance is the finish recommended for cabinetry and table tops. It is a satin finish for indoor use. Endurance is non-yellowing. Endurance needs one week to fully cure.

name: Clear Wax, CeCe Caldwell's
description: CeCe’s wax is a non-petroleum based, natural wax. In addition to being better for you, your family and the environment, it goes on smoothly without any drag or streaking. Made in the U.S.A

name: Aging Cream Dark, CeCe Caldwell's
description: 100% green, the Aging Cream, Dark is pre-tinted and can be used directly over CeCe paints for a rich aging, or over a Clear Wax for more subtle effect.  Made in the U.S.A

name: Aging Dust, CeCe Caldwell's
description: Soft powder that is used to add the appearance of natural aging to crevices, corners and crannies on pieces of furniture and picture frames. Easy to apply. Lightly sprinkle onto a newly waxed area and work into the crevices with a soft brush.  Use a soft rag to remove any excess.

name: Metallic Waxes, CeCe Caldwell's Wax
description:
Comes in Eldorado Gold and Sierra Silver 2 oz
Instructions for use: Apply a very thin coat of metallic wax to dry surface to highlight details or give shine. Additional wax can be applied to deepen the color. Allow wax to fully dry before use.

Ingredients: Beeswax, distilled mineral oil, non-toxic mica pigment
